'From Squeak 2.4b of April 23, 1999 on 30 July 1999 at 3:31:37 pm'!"Change Set:		PrimMakePoint-arDate:			30 July 1999Author:			Andreas RaabTwo modifications to primitiveMakePoint:a) Allow for non-integer arguments (which is okay, since 1@nil will return Point x: 1 y: nil).b) Allow float receivers so that float points can make use of the special byte code and don't have to go the long way."!!Interpreter methodsFor: 'arithmetic primitives' stamp: 'ar 7/30/1999 15:27'!primitiveMakePoint	| rcvr argument pt |	argument _ self stackValue: 0.	rcvr _ self stackValue: 1.	(self isIntegerObject: rcvr) ifTrue:[		(self isIntegerObject: argument)			ifTrue:[pt _ self makePointwithxValue: (self integerValueOf: rcvr)							yValue: (self integerValueOf: argument)]			ifFalse:[pt _ self makePointwithxValue: (self integerValueOf: rcvr)							yValue: 0.					self storePointer: 1 ofObject: pt withValue: argument].	] ifFalse:[		(self isFloatObject: rcvr) ifFalse:[^self success: false].		pt _ self makePointwithxValue: 0 yValue: 0.		self storePointer: 0 ofObject: pt withValue: rcvr.		self storePointer: 1 ofObject: pt withValue: argument.	].	self pop: 2.	self push: pt.! !